<dl id="n06053r"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06053r">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06053r"> 53(r)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> gronder</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">La poup&eacute;e est un des plus imp&eacute;rieux besoins et en m&ecirc;me temps un des plus charmants instincts de l&apos;enfance f&eacute;minine. Soigner, v&ecirc;tir, parer, habiller, d&eacute;shabiller, rhabiller <font color="green">[sic]</font>, enseigner, <mark>un peu gronder</mark>, bercer, dorloter, endormir, se figurer que quelque chose est quelqu&apos;un, tout l&apos;avenir de la femme est l&agrave;. <font color="green">[The doll is one of the most imperious needs and at the same time one of the most charming instincts of the female childhood. To care, to clothe, to dress, to dress, to undress, to dress, to teach, to scold, to cradle, to pamper, to sleep, to imagine that something is someone, the whole future of the woman is there.]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 119</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
